Modifications from upstream
---------------------------
- Removed all write capability: the HTTP client exposes only get/getBuffer
  (post/put/delete deleted) so the write surface cannot be reintroduced by
  accident. Read-only by construction.
- Added a BAMBOO_BASE_URL override so the server can be pointed at a
  loopback token-proxy, and made the BambooHR credential optional/injectable
  (proxy mode) rather than a hardcoded boot-time singleton.
- Conditional auth: no Authorization header is sent in proxy mode (the
  upstream proxy injects a fresh OAuth Bearer per request).

If read tools are later ported from other MIT-licensed BambooHR MCP
